"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-01-28-jamaican-students-dominate-2024-caribbean-stem-olympiads\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"JAMAICA earned two platinum medals, among the most prestigious, at the Caribbean STEM Olympiads' second annual event, held January 17-21 in a virtual format.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 7, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.999999993910933, \"rank\": 6.0886268946667565e-09, \"text\": \"JAMAICA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 71, \"end\": 80, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\", \"score\": 0.9999999999545253, \"rank\": 4.528224540242768e-11, \"text\": \"Caribbean\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\"}, {\"begin\": 81, \"end\": 85, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_STEM_fields\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7931318757827995e-17, \"text\": \"STEM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_STEM_fields\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_STEM_fields\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two platinum medals\", \"from\": 15, \"to\": 34}, {\"ngram\": \"a virtual format\", \"from\": 140, \"to\": 156}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Caribbean Science Foundation (CSF)-held event saw individuals and teams representing educational institutions, clubs, or themselves, competing in the math olympiad, computer coding olympiad, and robotics olympiad at three different age levels: 12-15, 16-18, and 19-21.\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 163, \"end\": 172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\", \"score\": 0.9999999999545253, \"rank\": 4.528224540242768e-11, \"text\": \"Caribbean\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CSF)-held event\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 208}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 224}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 234}, {\"ngram\": \"educational institutions\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 272}, {\"ngram\": \"clubs\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 279}, {\"ngram\": \"the math olympiad\", \"from\": 309, \"to\": 326}, {\"ngram\": \"three different age levels\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The math olympiad was held in aJeopardy-style format and covered topics ranging from consumer arithmetic to vector calculus.\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 557, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The math olympiad\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 450}, {\"ngram\": \"aJeopardy-style format\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 485}, {\"ngram\": \"topics\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 504}, {\"ngram\": \"consumer arithmetic\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 537}, {\"ngram\": \"vector calculus\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The computer coding olympiad tasked applicants with creating apps, games and websites aimed at solving a challenge faced by Caribbean communities.\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The computer\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 570}, {\"ngram\": \"olympiad tasked applicants\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 604}, {\"ngram\": \"apps\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 623}, {\"ngram\": \"games\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"websites\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 643}, {\"ngram\": \"a challenge\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"Caribbean communities\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The challenges tackled by teams in the 2024 olympiads included geohazards and climate change, inter- and intra-country transportation, public health, noncommunicable diseases, crime, and money movement and financial education.\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 931, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The challenges\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 719}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 olympiads\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"geohazards\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 797}, {\"ngram\": \"-country transportation\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 838}, {\"ngram\": \"public health\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"noncommunicable diseases\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"crime\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"money movement\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 906}, {\"ngram\": \"financial education\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The robotics olympiad tasked applicants with building innovative robots from kits (at Level I), and complex robots starting from scratch with a set of random parts at Level III.\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The robotics\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"tasked applicants\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"innovative robots\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"kits\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"Level\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1023}, {\"ngram\": \"complex robots\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1046}, {\"ngram\": \"scratch\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1068}, {\"ngram\": \"a set\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1079}, {\"ngram\": \"random parts\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"Level III\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1108}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of 131 students from 11 Caribbean countries registered for the 2024 olympiads.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1197, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A total\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1118}, {\"ngram\": \"131 students\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1134}, {\"ngram\": \"11 Caribbean countries\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1162}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 olympiads\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1196}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the preliminary rounds, 39 teams (83 students) made it to the finals.\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1273, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the preliminary rounds\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1226}, {\"ngram\": \"39 teams\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"83 students\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"the finals\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were 47 finalists in the math olympiad, 22 in the computer coding olympiad, and 14 in the robotics olympiad.\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1388, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"47 finalists\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1297}, {\"ngram\": \"the math olympiad\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"the computer coding olympiad\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"the robotics olympiad\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Medal certificates and cash prizes of US$500, $400, $300 and $200 were awarded to the teams winning platinum, gold, silver and bronze medals, respectively.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1544, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Medal certificates\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"cash prizes\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1423}, {\"ngram\": \"the teams\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1480}, {\"ngram\": \"platinum\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1503}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the awards and closing ceremony held January 21, Jamaica led the medal count with eight medals, followed by Antigua and Barbuda with six, Belize with four, Barbados with three, Saint Lucia with two, and Grenada, Guyana, Saint Kitts & Nevis and Trinidad &Tobago with one each.\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1598, \"end\": 1605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.999999993910933, \"rank\": 6.0886268946667565e-09, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1657, \"end\": 1664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antigua_and_Barbuda\", \"score\": 0.9995905336756523, \"rank\": 0.00040963405583722344, \"text\": \"Antigua\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antigua_and_Barbuda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antigua_and_Barbuda\"}, {\"begin\": 1726, \"end\": 1737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9704828944776312e-16, \"text\": \"Saint Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}, {\"begin\": 1752, \"end\": 1759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\", \"score\": 0.999999488787256, \"rank\": 5.112128586409703e-07, \"text\": \"Grenada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\"}, {\"begin\": 1761, \"end\": 1767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guyana\", \"score\": 0.998943246557681, \"rank\": 0.0009976648961924795, \"text\": \"Guyana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guyana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guyana\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the awards\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1559}, {\"ngram\": \"closing ceremony\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1580}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal count\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"eight medals\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"Barbuda\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1676}, {\"ngram\": \"Barbados\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1713}, {\"ngram\": \"Saint Kitts\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1780}, {\"ngram\": \"Nevis\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1788}, {\"ngram\": \"Trinidad\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1801}, {\"ngram\": \"Tobago\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1809}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Jamaican team, consisting of Chad Wright, Micah Edwards and Sidan-E Walker from Campion College, but who represented themselves, won the Level 1 math olympiad platinum medal.\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1830, \"end\": 1838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999815086087, \"rank\": 1.8491214926724638e-08, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1859, \"end\": 1870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_Wright\", \"score\": 0.9999953973730463, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chad Wright\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_Wright\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_Wright\"}, {\"begin\": 1898, \"end\": 1904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kemba_Walker\", \"score\": 0.9999999999636202, \"rank\": 3.6275466485376946e-11, \"text\": \"Walker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kemba_Walker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kemba_Walker\"}, {\"begin\": 1910, \"end\": 1925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Campion_College\", \"score\": 0.971969820659622, \"rank\": 0.028838528465244304, \"text\": \"Campion College\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Campion_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Campion_College\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Micah Edwards\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 1885}, {\"ngram\": \"the Level 1 math olympiad platinum medal\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 2003}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Michaela Brown, Jam\\u00eda Williamson, Kelsey Atkinstall and Kathryn McLean, also from Campion College but representing themselves, together won a platinu